      <hedline>
        <hl1>Rock of Ages</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Philip Blumberg letter on Gerald Marzorati's April 23 column on VH1 recalls his own brief encounter with channel</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Gerald Marzorati makes some superb points in his essay on VH1 (The Way We Live Now, April 23). I came of age in the 60's. One 20-second mistake represents the sum total of my VH1 viewership before I switched the channel; I saw Graham Nash, some of whose music I still admire. For the first 15 seconds, I was stupefied; for the next five seconds I was revolted. Turning off VH1 was a small triumph.</p>
        <p>Philip Blumberg  South Fallsburg, N.Y.</p>
      </block>
